45bool Symbol::is_private_brand() const {
46 bool value = Symbol::IsPrivateBrandBit::decode(flags());
47 DCHECK_IMPLIES(value, is_private());
48 return value;
49}

53 set_flags(Symbol::IsPrivateNameBit::update(flags(), true));
54 set_flags(Symbol::IsPrivateBrandBit::update(flags(), true));

70inline Tagged<Name> Name::cast(Tagged<Object> obj) {

75DEF_HEAP_OBJECT_PREDICATE(Name, IsUniqueName) {
76 uint32_t type = obj->map()->instance_type();
77 bool result = (type & (kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask)) !=
78 (kStringTag | kNotInternalizedTag);
79 SLOW_DCHECK(result == IsUniqueName(Tagged<HeapObject>::cast(obj)));
80 DCHECK_IMPLIES(result, obj->HasHashCode());
81 return result;
82}
83
84bool Name::Equals(Tagged<Name> other) {
85 if (other == this) return true;
86 if ((IsInternalizedString(this) && IsInternalizedString(other)) ||
87 IsSymbol(this) || IsSymbol(other)) {
88 return false;
89 }
90 return String::cast(this)->SlowEquals(String::cast(other));
91}
92
93bool Name::Equals(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Name> one, Handle<Name> two) {
94 if (one.is_identical_to(two)) return true;
95 if ((IsInternalizedString(*one) && IsInternalizedString(*two)) ||
96 IsSymbol(*one) || IsSymbol(*two)) {
97 return false;
98 }
99 return String::SlowEquals(isolate, Handle<String>::cast(one),
100 Handle<String>::cast(two));
101}

103// static
104bool Name::IsHashFieldComputed(uint32_t raw_hash_field) {
105 return (raw_hash_field & kHashNotComputedMask) == 0;
106}

108// static
109bool Name::IsHash(uint32_t raw_hash_field) {
110 return HashFieldTypeBits::decode(raw_hash_field) == HashFieldType::kHash;
111}

116 HashFieldType::kIntegerIndex;
117}

119// static
120bool Name::IsForwardingIndex(uint32_t raw_hash_field) {
121 return HashFieldTypeBits::decode(raw_hash_field) ==
122 HashFieldType::kForwardingIndex;
123}

125// static
126bool Name::IsInternalizedForwardingIndex(uint32_t raw_hash_field) {
127 return HashFieldTypeBits::decode(raw_hash_field) ==
128 HashFieldType::kForwardingIndex &&
129 IsInternalizedForwardingIndexBit::decode(raw_hash_field);
130}

132// static
133bool Name::IsExternalForwardingIndex(uint32_t raw_hash_field) {
134 return HashFieldTypeBits::decode(raw_hash_field) ==
135 HashFieldType::kForwardingIndex &&
136 IsExternalForwardingIndexBit::decode(raw_hash_field);
137}

139// static
140uint32_t Name::CreateHashFieldValue(uint32_t hash, HashFieldType type) {
141 DCHECK_NE(type, HashFieldType::kForwardingIndex);
142 return HashBits::encode(hash & HashBits::kMax) |
143 HashFieldTypeBits::encode(type);
144}
145// static
146uint32_t Name::CreateInternalizedForwardingIndex(uint32_t index) {
147 return ForwardingIndexValueBits::encode(index) |
148 IsExternalForwardingIndexBit::encode(false) |
149 IsInternalizedForwardingIndexBit::encode(true) |
150 HashFieldTypeBits::encode(HashFieldType::kForwardingIndex);
151}
152
153// static
154uint32_t Name::CreateExternalForwardingIndex(uint32_t index) {
155 return ForwardingIndexValueBits::encode(index) |
156 IsExternalForwardingIndexBit::encode(true) |
157 IsInternalizedForwardingIndexBit::encode(false) |
158 HashFieldTypeBits::encode(HashFieldType::kForwardingIndex);
159}

161bool Name::HasHashCode() const {
162 uint32_t field = raw_hash_field();
163 return IsHashFieldComputed(field) || IsForwardingIndex(field);
164}
165bool Name::HasForwardingIndex(AcquireLoadTag) const {
166 return IsForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad));
167}
168bool Name::HasInternalizedForwardingIndex(AcquireLoadTag) const {
169 return IsInternalizedForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad));
170}
171bool Name::HasExternalForwardingIndex(AcquireLoadTag) const {
172 return IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad));
173}

175uint32_t Name::GetRawHashFromForwardingTable(uint32_t raw_hash) const {
176 DCHECK(IsForwardingIndex(raw_hash));
177 // TODO(pthier): Add parameter for isolate so we don't need to calculate it.
178 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolateFromWritableObject(this);
179 const int index = ForwardingIndexValueBits::decode(raw_hash);
180 return isolate->string_forwarding_table()->GetRawHash(isolate, index);
181}
182
183uint32_t Name::EnsureRawHash() {
184 // Fast case: has hash code already been computed?
185 uint32_t field = raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
186 if (IsHashFieldComputed(field)) return field;
187 // The computed hash might be stored in the forwarding table.
188 if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsForwardingIndex(field))) {
189 return GetRawHashFromForwardingTable(field);
190 }
191 // Slow case: compute hash code and set it. Has to be a string.
192 return String::cast(this)->ComputeAndSetRawHash();
193}
194
195uint32_t Name::EnsureRawHash(
196 const SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded& access_guard) {
197 // Fast case: has hash code already been computed?
198 uint32_t field = raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
199 if (IsHashFieldComputed(field)) return field;
200 // The computed hash might be stored in the forwarding table.
201 if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsForwardingIndex(field))) {
202 return GetRawHashFromForwardingTable(field);
203 }
204 // Slow case: compute hash code and set it. Has to be a string.
205 return String::cast(this)->ComputeAndSetRawHash(access_guard);
206}
207
208uint32_t Name::RawHash() {
209 uint32_t field = raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
210 if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsForwardingIndex(field))) {
211 return GetRawHashFromForwardingTable(field);
212 }
213 return field;
214}
215
216uint32_t Name::EnsureHash() { return HashBits::decode(EnsureRawHash()); }
217
218uint32_t Name::EnsureHash(const SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded& access_guard) {
219 return HashBits::decode(EnsureRawHash(access_guard));
220}
221
222void Name::set_raw_hash_field_if_empty(uint32_t hash) {
223 uint32_t field_value = kEmptyHashField;
224 bool result = raw_hash_field_.compare_exchange_strong(field_value, hash);
225 USE(result);
226 // CAS can only fail if the string is shared or we use the forwarding table
227 // for all strings and the hash was already set (by another thread) or it is
228 // a forwarding index (that overwrites the previous hash).
229 // In all cases we don't want overwrite the old value, so we don't handle the
230 // failure case.
231 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!result, (String::cast(this)->IsShared() ||
232 v8_flags.always_use_string_forwarding_table) &&
233 (field_value == hash || IsForwardingIndex(hash)));
234}
235
236uint32_t Name::hash() const {
237 uint32_t field = raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
238 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsHashFieldComputed(field))) {
239 DCHECK(IsForwardingIndex(field));
240 return HashBits::decode(GetRawHashFromForwardingTable(field));
241 }
242 return HashBits::decode(field);
243}
244
245bool Name::TryGetHash(uint32_t* hash) const {
246 uint32_t field = raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
247 if (IsHashFieldComputed(field)) {
248 *hash = HashBits::decode(field);
249 return true;
250 }
251 if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsForwardingIndex(field))) {
252 *hash = HashBits::decode(GetRawHashFromForwardingTable(field));
253 return true;
254 }
255 return false;
256}

258bool Name::IsInteresting(Isolate* isolate) {
259 // TODO(ishell): consider using ReadOnlyRoots::IsNameForProtector() trick for
260 // these strings and interesting symbols.
261 return (IsSymbol(this) && Symbol::cast(this)->is_interesting_symbol()) ||
262 this == *isolate->factory()->toJSON_string() ||
263 this == *isolate->factory()->get_string();
264}

266bool Name::IsPrivate() {
267 return IsSymbol(this) && Symbol::cast(this)->is_private();
268}
269
270bool Name::IsPrivateName() {
271 bool is_private_name =
272 IsSymbol(this) && Symbol::cast(this)->is_private_name();
273 DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_private_name, IsPrivate());
274 return is_private_name;
275}
276
277bool Name::IsPrivateBrand() {
278 bool is_private_brand =
279 IsSymbol(this) && Symbol::cast(this)->is_private_brand();
280 DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_private_brand, IsPrivateName());
281 return is_private_brand;
282}
